item.title: Step 1 - Lets Talk
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
To get things going we will need to discuss your project. Providing me with the size, timeframe,  and a general or specific  description of your idea are a good start to a great mural.  

Phone me @ 832-457-0657 or
e-mail me: david@davidcobbmurals.com

item.title: Step 2 - Site Visit
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is a chance for us to meet and discuss the project at the planned site/space.  This  meeting also gives me a chance to see how  the painting will be incorporated into the existing space and give me a chance to take a few photographs.

After the visit I will complete a few rough sketches that I will send along with an estimate for the project. Usually I have that ready in a day or two.

item.title: Step 3 - Drawings
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Once the estimate has been approved and I’m given the green light, I will begin creating drawings. I will e-mail them to you as they are completed upon which you will review them and let me know what changes you would like to make. We continue this process until we agree on the drawings.All work to be painted will be drawn first and approved before work begins.

item.title: Step 4 - Let’s Paint
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Once a timeline is established and the drawings are complete, its time to paint! A 50% deposit is collected before work begins and the remaining is due upon completion.

For pricing and availablity please contact me:
david@davidcobbmurals.com
832-457-0657

item.title: THE BASIC PROCESS
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: The path to a great mural is not complicated, but it does require a fair amount of preparation. Depending on the project lead time can be as quick as a week, while larger projects can take a few months.  As always, I consider the process to be a collaborative effort and I always encourage input from my clients. The more ideas the better!

item.title: ABOUT
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
David Cobb Murals got its first project back in 2003 painting a 4’x 8’ sheet of plywood for my neighborhood swim team,  The Willow Wahoos!  It was a small project and it wasn‘t officially David Cobb Murals yet, but I was hooked to painting outside the studio.

I’ve always been a painter. Whether it was my parents house, my nieghbors fence, or art classes, painting has been my thing. I grew up learning handy man skills and worked for many years with professional contract painters mopping and gloping paint for commercial projects. Those skills have been a great aid in the quality of my work and efficiency on large projects.

With an emphasis in painting, I earned my bachelors degree from the University of Houston and have been painting consistantly since.  I remember being asked by one of my teachers upon graduation what I planned to do next. I already knew, “paint murals.”

I’ve had amazing response over the years for my work. I take a lot of pride in it and always want the next project to be my best! Whether painting animated characters for a pre-school or a highly rendered city scape for a model railroad, there's nothing I’d rather be doing than painting. Lets bring your ideas to life!
